## üìñ Overview

This repository houses the official implementation for the research article **"[Insert Your Paper Title Here]"**. 

Aerial imagery often presents a challenge: buildings look different when viewed from directly above (**Nadir**) versus from an angle (**Oblique**). Our work addresses this by leveraging fine-tuned **YOLOv8** architectures to create a robust segmentation pipeline that maintains high accuracy regardless of the viewing angle.

### ‚ú® Key Features
* **Angle Robustness:** distinctive performance on both top-down and angled imagery.
* **Efficiency:** Optimization of the YOLOv8-Seg architecture for speed/accuracy trade-offs.
* **Plug-and-Play:** Simple inference pipeline using standard weights.

---

## ‚öôÔ∏è Proposed Approach

Our methodology utilizes a modified encoder-decoder structure based on YOLOv8. The network is trained to generalize the concept of "building" across different perspective distortions.

<div align="center">
  <img src="path/to/your/approach_diagram.png" alt="Proposed Architecture" width="90%">
</div>

